Despite their efforts he drowned and was declared dead on the scene.The 29-year-old was in Durban as part of the SANDF contingent preparing for Armed Forces Day celebrations taking place next Tuesday.A police source said the man who has not been formally named was swimming at Battery Beach on the Golden Mile on Wednesday when he got into trouble."Lifeguards managed to pull him to shore where Netcare paramedics attempted to resuscitate him. However he was declared dead " he said.Various military personnel were on the scene which was described as sombre.This incident comes after another military official died when the tank he was seated in - which was on top of a military truck - was involved in an accident on its way to Durban.Armed Forces Day takes place on February 21 annually.